This paper focuses on the robustness of neural networks, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses adversarial attacks and defenses, which are relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computer security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper proposes a new method for training neural networks, which falls under the category of neural network optimization (cs.NE).
